<br>
The whole purpose of this thread is to stop fights, by removing ambiguity, and putting penalties in, for abuses of the system.<br>
<br>
You want a simple rule, fine... As long as you don't break that one simple rule, you don't have to deal with the mind boggling penalty rules.<br>
<br>
...<br>
<br>
The only conceivable reason for anyone to be against penalties, is that they in fact plan to break the agreement, and they don't want to suffer penalties for their actions.<br>
<br>
Unfortunately, that reasoning is flawed, since violating an agreement does carry other penalties, that add up over time in the form of bad feelings and resentment.<br>
<br>
If you think my original post was confusing, feel free to post your own modified version.<br>
<br>
Merloc <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ukaradin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Karadin</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>NB-GM</span><br>  Posts: 127<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(12/11/01 2:05:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=905.topic&index=53>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: bad</span><hr size=1> No Merloc, YOU are the one failing to grasp the simple concept.  And your logic is flawed.  NB has never violated our rotations.  We have no intentions ever violating our rotations.  We have passed when we needed to pass, we have always killed within 24 hours.  It's simple for us - if we can't do it tonight, it isn't happening.  Only guilds with morning crews run into that dangerous red zone of delaying X mob until the next day.  Yet I am against complicated penalties that involve people being forcibly skipped one or two times, etc.<br>
<br>
Even if NB never violates a rotation (which we haven't yet, nor will), *I* have to deal with all the complications that come with OTHERS violating rotations.<br>
<br>
I.E.  SoT went over on Tormax rotation, so now, they are out one time, but they killed after 24 hours, making it two times, so the rotation now looks like this: NB TL BOTS, NB TL BOTS SOT.  Now let's factor in all the other rotations NB is in: Doze/Named/Keeper/Statue/CT/Zland and who goofed what in where.  Now let's add all the patches in, and can you not understand why I wouldn't want to deal with needless penalties that can be avoided easily another way?<br>
<br>
Rotation rules simple:<br>
You get 24 hours, then it passes to next guild.<br>
<br>
Simple corallary: if you KNOW you can't do everything on your plate, it is common courtesy to pass the word to the next guild on rotation so they can have fair warning/something to do.<br>
<br>
If you missed it, you missed it.  It happens, have enough restraint to not break the rules.<br>
<br>
<br>
Merloc, less paranoia.  NB is against penalties, but not because we are out to cheat on rotations.  We are against them because they make unneeded complications to a guilds planning that doesn't violate rotations.<br>
<br>
Less rules, less complication, less ways for people to manipulate things.  I am more concerned about being led into breaking a violation of rotations by these kinds of complicated rules because someone else tells me the people before me are to be skipped.  More communication, less conflict, more honesty, and better evaluation of opportunities vs abilities is the answer.  Not more rules. <p><p><a href="http://www.noble-blade.net"><img src="http://www.noble-blade.net/images/ezboard/sig-small.gif" align="left" border="0"></a>Karadin Firethorne<br>Assassin of The Rathe<br><a href="http://www.noble-blade.net">Noble Blade</a> 
